      "content": "# external imports go in src reducer files not in SET_OPERATION_REDUCER\n\nThe `SET_OPERATION_REDUCER` MCP action receives only the reducer body — no imports, no function wrapper. If your reducer needs external utilities:\n\n1. Write the reducer body (without imports) in `SET_OPERATION_REDUCER`\n2. Add the import statements at the top of the actual file in `src/reducers/<module>.ts`\n\nSince [[reducer code goes into SET_OPERATION_REDUCER without function headers]], the MCP action only accepts the body. The src/ file is where the full module lives, including imports.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]\n- [[gotchas]]",
